25 LC 47 3597
House Bill 788
By: Representative Stinson of the 150th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to create a board of elections and registration for Macon County and to
2 provide for its powers and duties, approved June 3, 2003 (Ga. L. 2003, p. 4532), as amended,
3 particularly by an Act approved June 30, 2020 (Ga. L. 2020, p. 3946), so as to rename the
4 position of chief election official as the chief election supervisor; to provide that the county
5 manager shall supervise the nonelection duties of the chief election supervisor and other staff
6 of the election office; to provide that board members shall not undertake certain political
7 activities; to provide for board members to take the same oath as registrars; to revise
8 provisions relating to the meetings, minutes, and records of the board; to provide that the
9 governing authority of the county shall provide compensation to the board members, chief
10 election supervisor, and election staff; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
11 laws; and for other purposes.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
13 SECTION 1.
14 An Act to create a board of elections and registration for Macon County and to provide for
15 its powers and duties, approved June 3, 2003 (Ga. L. 2003, p. 4532), as amended, particularly
