16 by an Act approved June 30, 2020 (Ga. L. 2020, p. 3946), is amended by revising Sections 4
17 and 5 as follows:
18 "SECTION 4.
19 The board shall appoint a person to serve as the chief election supervisor of Macon County.
20 Such position shall be part time or full time as determined by the board and such person
21 shall be paid a salary to be set by the board and payable from county funds. The chief
22 election supervisor shall generally direct and control the administration of elections and
23 voter registration in Macon County. The board shall supervise the election related duties
24 of the chief election supervisor and all other election employees or staff. For all other
25 matters the chief election supervisor and election employees or staff shall be subject to the
26 supervision of the county manager. The chief election supervisor shall be subject to
27 removal from office by the board, with or without cause; provided, however, that the
28 county manager may recommend that the board remove the chief election supervisor for
29 deficiencies in the performance of nonelection related duties. The chief election supervisor
30 shall not be a member of the board nor an elected official.
31 SECTION 5.
32 Each member of the board shall:
33 (1) Serve for a term of four years and until a successor is appointed and qualified;
34 (2) Be eligible to be reappointed to succeed himself or herself and shall have the right
35 to resign at any time by giving written notice of such resignation to the commissioners
36 and to the clerk of the Superior Court of Macon County;
37 (3) Be subject to removal from the board at any time for cause, after notice and hearing,
38 by the chief judge of the Superior Court of Macon County;
39 (4) Not engage in political activity on behalf of any candidate, which shall include, but
40 not be limited to:
