41 (A) Distributing campaign literature;
42 (B) Engaging in any communication that advocates or criticizes a candidate or an
43 officeholder, including but not limited to social media; and
44 (C) Wearing badges, buttons, or clothing with partisan messages or displaying political
45 signage on vehicles if the signage is visible from or parked within 150 feet of the board
46 office or a designated polling place."
47 SECTION 2.
48 Said Act is further amended by revising Sections 7 and 8 as follows:
49 "SECTION 7.
50 In the event a vacancy occurs in the office of any member before the expiration of a term
51 by reason of removal, death, resignation, or otherwise, the appointing authority which is
52 required under Section 3 of this Act to make the appointment to the office upon expiration
53 of the term shall appoint a successor to serve for the remainder of the unexpired term in the
54 manner set forth in Section 3 of this Act.
55 SECTION 8.
56 Before entering upon the duties of office, each member shall take substantially the same
57 oath as required by law for county registrars and shall have the same privileges from
58 arrest."
59 SECTION 3.
60 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 15 as follows:
