61 "SECTION 15.
62 (a) The board shall fix and establish by appropriate resolution entered on its minutes
63 directives governing the execution of matters within its jurisdiction. The board shall hold
64 meetings at the county courthouse, at the courthouse annex, or at the place of meeting of
65 the commissioners no less than monthly. Any specially called meetings must be approved
66 by a majority vote of the board and shall be held only after the notification of the time and
67 place of the holding of such meeting has been communicated in writing to the chief
68 election supervisor to provide public notice of the meeting as required by law. All
69 meetings of whatever kind of the board shall be conducted pursuant to Chapter 14 of Title
70 50 of the O.C.G.A., relating to open meetings.
71 (b) The board shall maintain minutes of its meetings and a written record of policy
72 decisions that shall be amended to include additions or deletions. Such minutes and written
73 record shall be subject to Article 4 of Chapter 18 of Title 50 of the O.C.G.A., relating to
74 inspection of public records."
75 SECTION 4.
76 Said Act is further amended by revising subsection (b) of Section 16 as follows:
77 "(b) The members of the board shall receive compensation, in an amount determined by
78 the governing authority of the county, for their service as members of the board and shall
79 also be reimbursed for their actual and necessary expenses incurred in the performance of
80 their duties."
81 SECTION 5.
82 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 17 as follows:
